BuzzIntell™ Architecture Report
FDF Certified™ · BuzzWorld™ · Buzzomatic Intelligence LLC
Owner: Fredrick D. Flowers
Status: Architecture-First · Non-Authoritative · Signal-Only System
1. Executive Summary (Public-Facing)
BuzzIntell™ is a signal intelligence plane designed to observe identity-adjacent, contextual, and environmental signals and emit structured intelligence for downstream systems.
BuzzIntell does not enforce policy, manage secrets, authenticate identities, or execute actions.
It exists to inform, not to decide or act.
The system is intentionally positioned before authorization and enforcement, enabling safer, simpler, and more auditable decision-making downstream.
2. System Planes (Finalized)
Plane 1 — Signal Plane (BuzzIntell™)
Role: Observe & Emit
Authority: None
Correlates contextual signals (runtime, environment, BLE/network indicators, posture)
Normalizes inputs
Emits structured signals (assertions, scores, confidence)
Zero access, zero execution, zero secrets
Answers: “What is happening and under what conditions?”
Plane 2 — Policy Plane (PDP / ABAC / RBAC)
Role: Decide
Authority: Decision only
Consumes signals + verified identity
Applies static policies
Produces allow/deny + constraints
Answers: “Given verified identity and context, should this be allowed?”
Plane 3 — Enforcement Plane (PEP / Gateway / Mesh)
Role: Enforce
Authority: Control only
Enforces policy decisions
Allows or blocks traffic
Applies constraints
Answers: “How do we enforce this decision safely?”
Plane 4 — Capability Plane (BUZIT™)
Role: Execute
Authority: Bounded execution only
Executes pre-approved actions
No policy logic
No secrets
No escalation
Answers: “Given approval, what action is allowed to occur?”
Secrets Boundary (Out-of-Band)
Secrets Manager / HSM
Never accessible to BuzzIntell or BUZIT
Accessed only by Enforcement Plane post-approval
3. Interface Contracts (Locked)
Signal Contract
BuzzIntell → Policy Plane
Contains:
Context envelopes
Risk indicators
Confidence scores
Explicitly excludes:
Credentials
Tokens
Secrets
Permissions
Decision Contract
Policy Plane → Enforcement Plane
Contains:
Allow / Deny
Scope
Duration
Execution Contract
Enforcement Plane → BUZIT
Contains:
Approved capability
Limits
4. Trust Boundaries (Non-Negotiable)
BuzzIntell explicitly cannot:
Grant, deny, or modify access
Authenticate or authorize identities
Store, rotate, inject, or read secrets
Hold credentials or long-lived tokens
Escalate privileges
Bypass enforcement
Execute actions
Substitute for IAM, gateways, or vaults
These are architectural constraints, not configuration options.
5. STRIDE-Lite Threat Model (High Level)
Threat
Mitigation
Spoofing
Identity handled outside BuzzIntell
Tampering
Signals are read-only & signed
Repudiation
Decisions logged at Policy Plane
Information Disclosure
No secrets in Signal Plane
Denial of Service
Rate limits at Enforcement Plane
Elevation of Privilege
No cross-plane authority
6. Compliance Alignment (One-Page Mapping)
SOC 2
CC6.1: Logical access separated
CC6.6: Least privilege enforced by plane separation
CC7.x: Monitoring via signals only
ISO 27001
A.9: Access control isolated
A.12: Operational separation
A.14: Secure system architecture
BuzzIntell supports compliance by removing decision and execution from perception systems.
